    "title" : "Cyclomatic Complexity between deeply nested if statements and multiple separated if-conditions",
    "body" : "<p>I have a code snippet of deeply nested if statements and another code snippet of multiple separated if statements.\nThese 2 cases have same CC point.\nFollow <a href=\"https://pmd.github.io/pmd/pmd_rules_java_design.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">PMD</a> rule (Project Mistake Detector), could you explain why they are equal?\nDo you know why PMD rule design like this?\nIf CC is equal, how can I know which one is better?</p>\n<p>1/ Deeply nested if statements</p>\n<pre><code>if (A) { //+1\n   if (B) { //+1\n      if (C) { //+1\n         // do something\n      }\n   }\n}\n//-&gt; CC: 3\n</code></pre>\n<p>2/ Multiple separated if statements</p>\n<pre><code>if (A) { //+1\n   // do something\n}\nif (B) { //+1\n   // do something\n}\nif (C) { //+1\n   // do something\n}\n//-&gt; CC: 3\n</code></pre>\n",
