    "question_id" : 79550305,
    "body" : "<p>The usual way to define cyclomatic complexity of code is the number of linearly independent paths within it (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclomatic_complexity\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">source</a>). An <code>if</code> condition adds one additional path. This happens independently of whether it is nested or not.</p>\n",
